# config/no-mistakes-generation - local selection of the no-mistakes runtime
# generation for newly spawned ship tasks whose project mode is explicitly
# [no-mistakes]. Ignored for direct-PR, local-only, scout, and secondmate.
# Copy this into a local, gitignored config/no-mistakes-generation and edit.
# Do not commit captain-specific paths.
#
# Firstmate chooses the generation (binary + state root). No-mistakes chooses
# its own validation agents from fresh quota evidence inside that generation.
# Firstmate does not derive NO_MISTAKES_RUN_AGENTS from the crewmate harness.
#
# Format: key=value on non-empty, non-comment lines.
#   id=<short-label>              optional; defaults to the home basename
#   binary=<absolute-cli-path>    required
#   home=<absolute-state-root>    required (exported as NM_HOME)
#
# Absent file: ambient PATH no-mistakes and default NM_HOME (backward compatible).
# Present but invalid or unhealthy: fail closed at spawn with a diagnostic.
# Never silently routes to the ambient/default installation once selected.
#
# The resolved id/binary/home are snapshotted into each new task's meta and
# launch environment. A later config change affects only future tasks.
#
# Example (replace with the generation you stand up locally):
id=example-gen
binary=/absolute/path/to/versions/no-mistakes/example-gen/no-mistakes
home=/absolute/path/to/no-mistakes-gen-example
